Class NamedValueSelector

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants
    public class NamedValueSelector
extends javax.swing.JDialog
    The NamedValueSelector provides the user with list of values with a name associated with them. The NamedValueSelector is given two parallel arrays or Vectors with the value and the names in each.
    See Also:

      • isCancelled

        public boolean isCancelled()
        This is used to determine how the user closed the NamedValueSelector. If the user exits the dialog by any means other then by pressing the OK button, this is set to TRUE.
        Returns:
        FALSE if the user pressed the OK button.
